brew-unlock

Remove a stale Homebrew update lock file if the process that holds
it is no longer running.

Reads the PID from
`/opt/homebrew/var/homebrew/locks/update` (Apple Silicon) or
`/usr/local/var/homebrew/locks/update` (Intel). If `ps -p <pid>`
shows the process is still alive, the lock is left in place;
otherwise both lock paths are removed.

Useful when `brew update` was killed mid-run and subsequent
invocations refuse to proceed because of the stale lock.
